# The Best Fried-Eggplant Sandwich Recipe

![](B77FEBC0-AAD9-49F3-9999-455688359B5D.jpg)

## Ingredients

- Eggplants | 2 smallish | Pealed & sliced vertically

Let stand for approximately 10 to 15 minutes and pat dry

- Olive Oil | 1 cup extra-virgin | 

Heat oil in a wide pot

Partially fry eggplant for 30 to 40 seconds per side

- Salt | 2 tablespoons kosher | 
- Eggs | 4 large | 
- 2  Tablespoons Grated Parmesan Cheese |  | 

Whisk together

Dip eggplant into egg batter, then fry in oil until puffed, lightly golden and cooked through, approximately 2 to 4 minutes per batch

